<MSG
Phew...<NOD<CLRThat was quite the display!<NOD
I knew I was right to entrust my
first =Spur= with you.<NOD
If only I were a little younger...<NOD
And, well, armed...<NOD<CLROh, no, don't worry about me.<NOD
He only threw me around a
little bit.<NOD Between you and
me I think he smashed up the
ceiling just to intimidate you.<NOD<CLRWhat I'm really worried about
is my tools, and...<GIT0002<NOD<CLR
Oh, you brought it!<NOD<GIT0000<CLRGood, good.<NOD Lemme just
regain my composure, and I'll
fix it up in a moment.<NOD<CLO<FAO0001<WAI0150<FAI0001
<FLA<WAI0050<TAM0002:0013:0000<MSG<CMU0010<GIT0013
=Polar Star= became the =Spur=!<SMC<DNP0210<WAI0160<NOD<CMU0008<FL+0340<END
#0203
<MSG
Uhff...<NOD My back...<NOD<CLR
...You!?<NOD<CLRI saw you in that fight!<NOD
You're the one who stole my
=Polar Star=!<NOD<GIT0002 Give that back!<NOD<GIT0000<CLRI toiled weeks on end to put
together this prototype after
the last one was stolen!<NOD
And let me guess, you stole
that one too, didn't you?<NOD<CLR
......<NOD<CLRYou know...<NOD
I've long believed that one's
weapons should be crafted by
oneself.<NOD
That one who fights with another's
weapons and considers that force
his own is witless.<NOD
That one who blames his tools for
that which his own power cannot
achieve is a fool...<NOD<CLR
<CMU0008But...<WAI0050<CLRWhen I see this gun before me that
you have used so exhaustively,
it moves this man to tears.<NOD
To think such thorough use were
possible even before the gun's
completion...<NOD
And to think my life would be
saved by it as well...<NOD<CLR
Hahhh...<NOD<CLR
I apologize for my grumbling.<NOD<CLRYou can keep this gun.<NOD<CMU0000<FAO0001
After I finish it, of course...<NOD<CLO<ITJ0005:0206<WAI0150<FAI0001
<FLA<WAI0050<TAM0002:0013:0000<MSG<CMU0010<GIT0013
=Polar Star= became the =Spur=!<SMC<DNP0210<WAI0160<NOD<CMU0008<FL+0340<END
#0204
<KEY<MSGI should be more upset about
my house, but I'm not.<NOD
After seeing all around the
island when I was looking for
just that one part...<NOD<CLRWell, I can safely say I'm
glad to be entrusting my life's
work with you.<NOD Keep them
safe, you hear?<NOD<END
#0205
<KEY<MSGIn this world, there exists a
balance between those who are
creators and those who are users.<NOD<CLRI knew that, of course, but
it took your help for me to
experience this firsthand.<NOD
From now on, I vow to dedicate
myself to the side of creation.<NOD
The labor involved becomes joy
when I know there are those who
will enjoy my work to the utmost.<NOD<END
